(69,	1,	'WELL CALCIUM COMPLEX',	'&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Calcium is essential for maintaining body \r\nhealth. Your body needs it every day not just to keep your bones and \r\nteeth strong over your lifetime, but to ensure proper functioning of \r\nmuscles and nerves. Well Calcium Complex helps to maintain normal bone \r\ndensity and development. It not only contains Calcium but also other \r\nvital nutrients like Vitamin D, Magnesium, Vitamin K2-7 and Zinc that \r\npromotes bone health and gives body a strong foundation.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Features &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;CALCIUM\r\n CITRATE MALEATE: One of the most effective and bio-available forms of \r\ncalcium that helps maintain normal bone density and development&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;MAGNESIUM: Helps in bone structure and biochemical reactions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;VITAMIN D: Helps optimise calcium absorption&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;VITAMIN\r\n K2-7: Helps in flow of calcium from blood stream to bones. May help to \r\ninhibit arterial calcification and promote cardiovascular health.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;ZINC: Helps in metabolic functions and strengthens immunity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Potential&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Users&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Children,\r\n women, adolescents, elderly men &amp;amp; women who have increased need of \r\ncalcium, magnesium and Vitamin D or whose dietary intake of these \r\nnutrients is low.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;General Information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bones\r\n are living tissues and throughout life, they experience remodeling, \r\nsince old bone tissue gets worn-out and fresh bone is produced. We reach\r\n our maximum bone strength by about the age of 30 years. After that we \r\nslowly start losing our bones as our body absorbs less of calcium with \r\nthe age. Calcium is essential for maintaining body health. A body, \r\nstores about 99 percent of its calcium in the bones and teeth to help \r\nmake and keep them strong. Our body needs calcium intake every day, not \r\njust to keep our bones and teeth strong for our lifetime, but to ensure \r\nproper functioning of our muscles and nerves as well. Calcium deficiency\r\n is usually due to an inadequate intake of calcium. When blood calcium \r\nlevels drop too low, the vital mineral is &quot;borrowed&quot; from the bones. If \r\nan individual\'s calcium intake in diet is low, there may not be \r\nsufficient amount of calcium available in the blood to be returned to \r\nthe bones to maintain strong bones and body health.Therefore healthy \r\nactions to promote bone health should begin in childhood and continue \r\nthroughout our lifetime.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*Adequate Calcium and\r\n Vitamin D throughout life, as part of a well-balanced diet, may reduce \r\nthe risk of osteoporosis. (The U.S. Food and Drug Administration \r\nauthorized a health claim related to Calcium, Vitamin D and Osteoporosis\r\n for foods and supplements)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;Caution&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;Modicare\r\n Well Calcium Complex is a food supplement and is not indented to \r\ndiagnose, treat, cure or prevent any disease. People with specific \r\nmedical conditions, pregnant and lactating women are recommended to \r\nconsult their doctor before taking the dietary supplement.&lt;/p&gt;',	'WELL CALCIUM COMPLEX',	'WELL CALCIUM COMPLEX',	'WELL CALCIUM COMPLEX',	'WELL CALCIUM COMPLEX'),
